OL,3,C405-line switch-off and similarities
OL,4,Cwith present day service closures
OL,6,FEvery TV manufactured from 1964 ` and
OL,7,Fmany made immediately before ` was
OL,8,Fcapable of receiving a UHF 625-line
OL,9,Fservice. (A few sold before BBC Two
OL,10,Fbecame widely available, it should be
OL,11,Fnoted, did require modification first
OL,12,Fthough.)
OL,14,FOnce BBC One and ITV became available
OL,15,Fon UHF too from November 1969 onwards,
OL,16,Fthe fate of 405-line was finally
OL,17,Fsealed.
OL,19,FGradually older sets fell out of use.
OL,20,FSome simply failed. Others were
OL,21,Freplaced as their owners wanted to
OL,22,Fupgrade to get BBC Two or colour.
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/9
