OL,3,C405-line switch-off and similarities
OL,4,Cwith present day service closures
OL,6,FBut the broadcasters and the
OL,7,Fgovernment stuck to the spirit of
OL,8,Fcommitments made in the 60s that
OL,9,Fnobody would be forced to replace a
OL,10,Fworking 405-line set.
OL,12,FFrom around 1982, VHF relays were
OL,13,Fgradually turned off. Virtually nobody
OL,14,Fnoticed. Then came the switch-off of
OL,15,Fthe main transmitters in January 1985.
OL,17,FRealistically, it could all have
OL,18,Fhappened much earlier but for the
OL,19,Fdecision to keep faith with those who
OL,20,Fowned old sets.
