OL,3,C405-line switch-off and similarities
OL,4,Cwith present day service closures
OL,6,FThere can be hardly anyone left
OL,7,Flistening to R4 LW. But the BBC has
OL,8,Fbeen exceptionally, arguably unduly,
OL,9,Fcautious ending broadcasting on the
OL,10,Ffrequency. Even if the signal was
OL,11,Fstill broadcast for the sake of the
OL,12,Fenergy companies, programmes could
OL,13,Fhave been replaced by a recorded loop
OL,14,For the tone.
OL,16,FMeanwhile moves announced in 2022 to
OL,17,Fmake BBC Four, CBBC and Radio 4 Extra
OL,18,Fonline only services seem to have been
OL,19,Fquietly kicked into the long grass.
OL,21,FIt may still happen one day but there
OL,22,Fare no signs of a shutdown in 2025.
